&lt;p&gt;Given an integer arrayÂ &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt;, returnÂ &lt;em&gt;the sum of divisors of the integers in that array that have exactly four divisors&lt;/em&gt;. If there is no such integer in the array, returnÂ &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example 1:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [21,4,7]&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 32&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;
